caption: What I like about this place is the food and the people working here. Staff are amazing  and this place is very cozy.

Tried messy breakfast. Doesn't provide condiments like jam for the muffins. Butter provided is melted instead of cold frozen butter. Muffin is too oily.  Sausage feels jelak after eating. Having a bad stomach after eating it suffering from acid reflux. Hope that the restaurant gone through food safe certification course. Still unsure if food served is fresh and properly handled.  Scrambled egg tasted weird with a strong herbs taste rather than any other brunch cafes buttery smell. Coffee is quite good.
Very good service and I love the complimentary fruit juice served in test tubes! Super cool place and their fish n chips are really crispy~  For detailed review checkout ig:@yun.eats
Extra points for complimentary fruit juice served in test tubes, water served in beakers, and color scheme used. Much effort put into plating and decent serving.
Ambience is gd n quiet!
Great food at reasonable prices. Good place for a lazy afternoon
Great place for brunches. Must try include the Messy Breakfast and the Lychee white chocolate cake....unbelievable Happy hour on beer 4$ Perfect lazy afternoon
Nice cozy place
Interesting concept food joint. Cosy and relax. Food is good but slightly on pricier side. Went for lunch. Perhaps will try their breakfast.

One of the rare find in Kembangan area. Very good service, coffee is unbelievably good. Food is good too. Prices are bit on higher side but really worth every cent. You get a complementary mixed fruit drink which is refreshing
Still maintaining their food quality and service standard üëç
Good da bomb

Cosy cafe with an interesting concept. Was there for the first time and was served juice samplers in test tubes and water in beakers. However, their food didn‚Äôt impress. The lychee cake in particular wasn‚Äôt fresh and their mango cake was just so-so. Not a place I will patronise again.

Went to fresh fruits labs for brunch. Cosy place. The pastel colour palette and deco of the cafe is fun and unconventional. Upon arrival we were given fruit juices served in test tubes on the house. The Messy breakfast was yummy and one of the more affordable brunches in Singapore. The drinks were good. Not photographed is the chocolate overload cake it was devoured too quickly. The couple at the next table had fish and chips and some pretty juices which I can‚Äôt take off my mind. Great food, good prices. Will be back (hopefully tomorrow).

Tried messy breakfast. It's good. Iced mocha, not so much. Coffee is really below average compared to other cafes. Prices are without 17% taxes. With the taxes, price to food ratio is below average. Service is good though. Probably will recommend food selection but not the coffee, given the prices.

Great place to go for a lazy Sunday brunch. Had a "messy breakfast" and it was really very decent and satisfying. My niece,who happens to be a somewhat picky eater, finished her soft shell crab pasta and actually asked for seconds. Her younger brother also polished off almost 3/4 of his own messy breakfast order, which was a feat in its own right as he is a very light eater. The missus ordered the pork chops which were tasty enough but not as fork tender as we would have liked,being a little on the chewy,slightly tough side.  All in, a great place for bringing young-uns,or just to while the afternoon away while enjoying a nice cold one.üòÜ

Food was very good. The messy breakfast tasted genuine unlike some local imitations of English breakfasts. Service was good as waitresses were very friendly. General atmosphere is light and not too noisy. Would recommend to those looking for a place to have brunch in the east.
Dishes were tasty! Ambience is soothing and service is excellent!
Decent food and superb customer service. Plus, you can even use Burpple deals to get your money‚Äôs worth!
Quiet during the CCB period. Prices a bit high for the quantity but other than that, its a nice place to chill.

A sparkly, unicorn-y, hello-kitty, fruit juice in a test tube sort of place. Simple good salads, western fare (fish and chips, pasta, chicken wings), with a smile, a bit of whimsy, and a pastel colored deco vibe.
Amazing food, nice ambience and staff are very friendly! Overall a fantastic place to dine in .

Super fun place to bring your kids. There's a play area that doesn't really look like much but the kids will entertain themselves for hours or as long as you take to eat. Surprisingly very good food!!!!!! And in line with their theme, each table gets a little selection of welcome drinks (fresh juices) served in test tubes. So adorable. Dessert is sooooooo yum. Pretty good selection of food on menu and there's a lunch and dinner promotion on most of the time.
The food here was good and the portions are big.
Very nice food and good service.

Very good burger, great happy hour rates on beer... Really weird restaurant theme. Random hospital objects and plushies everywhere which don't make sense at all. Feels like the utensils were taken either from a chemistry lab or old Changi hospital. Stayed away for so many years thinking it's a vegan fruit place due to it's name but was pleasantly surprised with the food, will be back!

Great ambience, quiet and pleasant. Next to small roads so no loud traffic. Soft pop cover music.  The food was fantastic! When you sit down they bring you fruit juice samples in test tubes and you drink out of beakers. Overall the theme and setting is great.  The burger was juicy, and had a very nice smell of cumin. Dory was very nice as well. I really like the fruit salad in the burger.  If you come on a weekday. The set lunch is only $12++.
Had their set lunch. Their tomato soup is worse than canned tomatoes soup. Salty and extremely watery.
Food is delicious . Red velvet couldn't complaint and nice vibe environment. Worth another visit
Nice and cosy. Not too crowded which made the experience wonderful.
They provide free test tubes of juices. Feels like I'm back in school. Pork chop was the bomb.
Pork chop is awesome and its great to wssh down with a glass of freshly pressed juice. Gives u a satisfying meal leaving you feeling fresh
i really liked their fruits theme. was served with a refreshing shot when we sat down and their eggs benedict was really delicious
Great deal with Burpple Beyond
Always enjoyed dining here. The pork chop is da bomb

Very cool concept, super aesthetic and cute place with pink and light blue decorations , has high tables outside. Every table comes with a soft toy sitting on the chair so it's so cute. Staff was v friendly and the menu was also super pretty. There's a weekday lunch set frm 11pm to 3pm and it's 12+++ quite worth it but only have 3 choices
Interesting concept, pretty decent taste, good ambience with cushions.
Nice place for dining, not expensive
Beautiful and calm place with many artistic cakes as well as well as healthy fruit juices!! A place for friends and families to chill and enjoy the clean, spacious feel with healthy juices!!
Great food, good price. Big portions. Value for money.
Better than your typical hipster cafe. Always good!

Second time here and it is still as fantastic. Service with a smile and the quality of the food never ceases to amaze me. Usually cafes have pretty meh bites but portions with FFL were not only big but the ingredients used, presentation of the dish and taste of the food exceeds my expectations time and again.  Great for groups, gatherings and for chilling. I highly recommend and will definitely be going back for more!
Really nice food and kind customer service. ü§§üëç
Good happy hour rates. Children friendly. Highly recommended for parents with kids
Loved the flat white, and the pancakes.

You would think that they'll be focusing on their fruit related menu because of their name. But you'll be surprised by their non fruit related main dishes. They're amazing. We tried their fish and chips, as well as the classic pork chops. The food presentation was superb, tasted great and priced reasonably! (No service charge even!)
A nice to have drink and happy hour at reasonable price
Relaxed kids friendly ambience with rather generous servings, i had the beef burger and was definitely full post meal. Price was reasonable for a location away from the usual brunch spots in Katong
Like the juices and decoration of Fresh Fruits Lab. Happy that able to sit out with my dog
The place is quite cozy, nicely decorated with some soft toys :) Free fruit drink is given in test tubes, which makes it kind of cute too but the prices are not that cheap
Interesting I read on the net that some people only eat fruits. They call themselves fruitarian I believe. I am not recommending the practice as I am not a dietician
Great food. Worth a try, and returning for more too.

My favourite cafe in SG. It serves delicious food consistently and never disappoints each time I visit. I love the masago caviar pasta the most here, it‚Äôs my go-to pasta. It was my friend‚Äôs first visit to the cafe and she loved the quality of the food here. She thoroughly enjoyed her salmon steak!  We went on a weekday for dinner, so we had free dessert and soup of the day with every main course ordered. The carrot soup was yummy! (:
Had a great ribeye steak for dinner, done very well. Great sliders and the little miss koala sandwich was fabulous. Will definitely return.
The salad was very fresh and the burger taste so good. Cosy ambience. Great place to chill.
Always great food, delicious tasting coffee server by nice, pleasant people. Keep up the good work guys!
Nice ambience to hang around. Alot of photo worthy props
The food was quite nice actually but the place itself felt kinda bland
Great place! Great food very attentive staff!

We had to sit outside as we had a puppy with us but the female staff was friendly, and very helpful in turning on the fans.  They also give complimentary fruit juices in test tubes, while water is served in lab beakers.  We ordered two lunch specials, comprising chicken burger and aglio olio pasta with deep fried otah.   The burger was a generous portion, and the fries were good.  Unlike mot other places, the buns did not turn out soggy at all, and I loved the two sliced pickles.  Though deep fried, the chicken was not dry.  The pasta (you have a choice of penne or spaghetti) looked spicy,  but was not.  I liked the deep fried otah, but the aglio olio sauce with minced otah was a tad bland for me.  The sets came with pumpkin soup, which tasted great.  For $2 more each, you can select an artisan tea.
This is our favourite cafe in the entire east. They serve excellent coffee, besides having a great brunch menu with very good portions.
Parking was ample on a weekday. Nice environment. Food is pretty good. Service above average.
Amazing burger and salad was good. Fries I left over, as I deny potatoes. But all in all very good

Been there twice for breakfast and dinner. Food was great on both occasions but personally preferred their dinner menu. Prices slightly on the higher side but still reasonable l. Great service and friendly staff.
Great place for family brunch
Great place and it's pet friendly.
Happy ambience , nice theme. Average quality food. Not much fruits or juices to match the name of the place. The fries were lousy.
Good location? simple and cosy. Crew is really friendly and kind though kinda slow. Coffee was excellent. Worthy of support.

Cafes are usually not known for their steaks, but FFL‚Äôs Angus Rib Eye is definitely worth its price. It‚Äôs a genuine 250gm of Angus rib-eye that‚Äôs tender and soft, with the perfect amount of chew before easily sliding down your throat. It‚Äôs also served alongside thin-cut truffle fries instead of your regular fries.
Nice little cafe with nice food only setback is slow service always!!! üò§

Had a meal with my girls here. I had pork chop, my queen messy brunch and a teddy meal for my princess. I like the fact that the place is child friendly. Food wise, I enjoyed my pork chop as it was well marinated and tender. Serving is decent too. My queen got the brunch and I tasted it, I didn't really like the sausages as they were a little light on flavour. Overall, I enjoyed my time here.
Awesome food and environment
Cosy and reasonable price
Love pork chops
Healthy foods & drinks.
Burger was great but overpriced. Flat white coffee was average at best
This is amazing place.. very creative and artistic with very affordable foods and drinks and healthy..

Good place but quite expensive for the neighborhood. Good choices of cakes, and smiling staff :)  I have tried the brunch and there are some good options. Unfortunetaly, all the Eggs options contains bacon or chicken, so it's not Vegetarian friendly . They have nice juice and serve them in funny containers. But with Plastic straw ... They have a nice menu for hot drinks, with options like Purple Sweet potato latte !
Great place for family gathering
Decent food; go here often. Eggs Benedict are nice.

A quaint little cafe that makes little girls go 'wow'. You will be greeted with samples of juices to try, all filled in test tube. Kids menu is healthy and delicious. Be sure to try their fruit juices.

Great spot with cute decor, and great food and drink. Can't beat the price either! A sample juice, a soda, a meal, and a little ice cream at the end for $18. It also had lots of toys for kids if you wanted to bring family.

When you come in and order, they give you a "shot" of juice in a test tube, testament to its name. Its a nice touch.  Drinks are okay, coffee and juices are all good. Food is decent, but I feel like their standards have dropped over the years. The brunch menu items are still cheaper than average, but the taste has kind of gotten worse from previous years...

Excellent Sunday breakfast with my family, initially my wife was shocked when I mentioned the name as she thought it was a fruits shop. Haha but the breakfast we had were way more delicious and fruity than we expected. Totally worth it and even my daughter was able to finish the pancakes she ordered. Will be back again on weekends. Oh yeah ambience is also very family oriented and can't forget the interesting test tubes as well. :)
Solid western style food with a few twists. Family friendly and consistent.

Nice, healthy food options. Very reasonable prices and portions. Ok service.  I got the scallop and caviar pasta on a whim. First mouth was ok, but each following bite seemed to get better and better. It‚Äôs pretty savoury and somehow creamy (though I don‚Äôt recall cream being on the list of ingredients). Extremely generous with the Icelandic caviar and 3 whole scallops. I might be biased, because I love caviar so every bite was a pop of joy in my mouth! The creaminess probably came from all the caviar. The pasta was a tad rich after awhile but not so bad that I couldn‚Äôt finish it.  Can‚Äôt comment on their signature Blackstone breakfast as I didn‚Äôt have it, but my partner seemed to relish it. The portion for that seemed smaller than the last time we went, though..
hungry but sadly not appetizing. service was great tho!
Uniquely furnished, creative menu, cosy comfy atmosphere. Drinks served in lab-like utensils like test tubes, beakers.

Great ambience! Very cosy, vibrant and colourful!:) Awesome place to go with friends for a lunch! Set lunch only for $12. Must try the Lychee cake. Yummmmmy! Staff is super friendly too. The only drawback is the location which is not in a high foot fall location. Rest all thumbs up!
Good food. Friendly staff.
Great service and place is kids friendly. Love it
Acceptable food quality. Service was a little haphazard. Room for some improvement.
Great food & services
Cuteness overload here
the best place yet for poached eggs in singapore. a must try place for brunch or breakfast. their coffees are great. they also have a couple of unique flavors to offer in their drinks menu.
a wonderful high tea special. everything is scientific lab themed
Nice place. Good food. Drinks are overpriced and overhyped. Great for kids!
Food not bad....can bring along pets

(Translated by Google) A great, unusual restaurant. Kitchen in the style of the laboratory, cleanliness, attention to taste, aesthetics, extremely friendly service. A very good place to go eat something with children. In principle, I do not like cold coffee, but what they say has changed my opinion on the subject. RECOMMEND! nice food n environment here

An experimental and kiddy experience! Definitely great for weekday afterwork chill. Quiet, fresh, sweet and homey. Ordered veggie wrap. It came warm, juicy, soft and comfy. The orange juice served in a testing tube was simply a lovely surprise!

Came in to try its food & we‚Äôre surprised that they serve the high tea menu on a Sunday (read on website that it‚Äôs not available on Sunday). The food items were very nice, although we find the sweet items were too much. But it was all nice & the layout was interesting. Would like to come back to try the food for lunch & dinner.
Great fresh salads! Vegeterian friendly and good staff service!

High Tea was fantastic. The place was clean and quirky and were served quickly with plenty of fruit infused water. Science themed High Tea included: Drinks Choice of tea or flavoured soda  Savoury Duck wraps Grilled watermelon Prawn salad cocktail Bacon wrapped asparagus on toast  Sweet Rainbow cake Salted caramel chocolate lava cake Shortbread with fresh fruit and mango pur√©e Macaron  All made with fresh ingredients and beautifully presented in science equipment, measuring beakers, test tubes, evaporation trays etc  At $S38 for 2 people, it was fantastic value in a pricey city. The only tiny criticism is that boyfriend would have liked more tea, he only got one cup and we're used to a pot being served on other teas we have tried.  Thanks FFL
Love this place! Food, ambience, location, perfect :)
Good caf√© food. Truffle fries is nice. Average spending for 1 pax is 20-30sgd.
Food....average. Good service . Pleasant enviroment
Overall the food is nice. Service is good.
Right down my place, has weekday and weekend menus. Friendly service, good food and great ambience. Was skeptical at first but now its one of my fave places in the east

A refreshing place on a hot Singapore‚Äôs day. Stepping into the no frills pastel coloured cafe somehow provide ones mind a cooling down effect. Stuffed toys and clinical gadgets like stathoscopes seems to litter some of the tables. On completion of your food order, a set of fruit juice filled test tubes are presented to you for your refreshments. We had fun trying to decipher the contents of the juices. The food were good size potions and I loved the tea selections, and how it was served in. It is child friendly so don‚Äôt be surprised to see lots of Birthday celebration taking place.
Coffee and tea is good.  Personally feel the dessert cakes can get better. Mousse is a skip,  too moist and needs more flavor and depth.
Great food and environment

Objectively the second best diner in Singapore, Fresh Fruits Lab has all the relaxed atmosphere of a cafe and none of the outrageous prices. FFL has a light science theme, with complimentary fruit juice samples in test tubes and water served in beakers. Nestled in every chair is a child friendly pillow, such as a unicorn or a smiling slice of watermelon. The food is delightful and served in big portions. Overall a great choice, though Carl's junior remains a better and cheaper place to eat.

Really nice ambience and decorations. Piccolo tea and truffle fries were good. Fish and chips was 7/10. Soft shell crab pasta was 5/10. The Chili crab sauce for the pasta was overly sweet and tasted more like ketchup, it was not really savoury. The soft shell crab was not fresh at all and really fishy.
My favourite Spicy Aglio Olio with grilled chicken
Novelty experience of serving drinks in test tubes and beakers but short on taste. Low CP
amazing food and service!
It's all too good. Happy hour on the blonde too.
Very chill caf√© great for meet ups. They serve unique fruit juice in test tubes. The food is not too bad although nothing mind blowing.
A great place to have some good brunch
Nicely decorated cafe, feels homely. Chairs are not very comfortable though. Food is ok, juices are served in lab apparatus. Prices are a little high
Delicious!
CFL at FFL
Friendly staff and interesting food!
Just ordered a coffee there for take away, so far service staff is very friendly and attentive.
Friendly waitress that always service with a smile

A great place for weekend hangouts especially with toddlers, though space is rather limited during peak hours. There's a kids' corner to help keep them busy.  The complimentary juice tubes are definitely a highlight, and they are actually all quite tasty. The food is okay, mostly healthy, though the egg benedicts can be better improved in egg texture.  Make sure to make your reservation on weekends as tables are only a few, and the place can be rather crowded.

It is usually a weekly outing for us to have dinner or lunch here. It can get a bit noisy when they restaurant is full especially with many kids. The children can enjoy the toys and the staffs are very nice. Food is absolutely affordable and the must try is the truffle fries. The portion is big and it tastes heavenly.

Love the ambience and food offer. The juices are so nice and at times were distributed as complimentary drinks. There are props available for photo taking. Very interesting concept. A good place to go during weekends and brunch. Will definitely be back.
Happy place for children and unicorns.üòÅ
Nice cosy place with space for kids to play and a good tasty food
Cool off the script experience. Great detox juices after a hard night of drinking. Food was cheaper than expected, nice staff.

Fresh Fruits Labs is nice and has a very interesting concept. The whole place is designed like a lab with water given in beakers and juice shots served in test tubes once you get seated. Overall the food is nice and not too expensive! Their coffees and pancakes are delicious. The place attracts crowds over the weekends. Being close to my home I go there frequently!
Love this place. Like the food menu and the ambience. Service is good too.

interesting fruit juice serving but the food is.......ok lah not cheap for a family of 4 but if for the fun of drinkin your juices in test tube.... i give then a thumbs up for the innovation in dining.
Juices here are highly recommended
Soft crab pasta is tasty and they have nice main menu too for dinner

The setup is cosy yet lively. The cutlery is quirky .. sticking to it's name you'll be served in beakers, test tubes and flasks. The food is really. Staff is friendly and even helps with recommendations. Must visit and a place that can become a habit.
Amazing juice and pancakes. Nice concept of serving food in chemistry lab equipments.
Nice place

Very sweet and cosy deco! Most importantly the service staffs were so friendly and attentive! Food was also yummy! Will definitely come by more often! They have a children play corner as well! And also complimentary fruits juice served in test tubes!
The outlet have just undergo a renovation not very long ago. It's brighter now but previous the old table and chairs. The quality of the brunch seems to have  dropped. Kind of disappointed.

Food is nice and price is reasonable. It gets pretty crowded over the weekends and reservation is strongly encouraged. You must try the truffle fries and I like the Fish and Chip. My wife likes the Cajun Chicken.
Complementary fruit juice and water upon being seated, big portions at affordable price
Great options for breakfast, brunch and lunch. Some cool toys for kids. Love their juices.

(Translated by Google) It's close enough to walk from Kusen Road and it's on Changi Road so it's quite easy to understand. The freshly squeezed fruit juice, colorful cakes, and one-plate menus like cafe rice were very delicious. There are so many Japanese people on Kusen Road, but it was a strange feeling because there was no Japanese other than me. Just OK

The interior is very cute, they have stuffed toys and medical accessories everywhere.  They serve welcome drinks of fresh fruit juice in test tubes for every table, but other than that I don't really see the fresh fruit theme of this restaurant other than they include a few sliced fruits with every meal.  Be careful, as the stethoscopes scattered around the restaurant are real, so don't let your kids play with them unsupervised.
Salad was small, cake did not have enough flavor, was more like a white chocolate cake then a mango. Hubby's brunch plate was genius and tasted much better than my salad.
Good food and great atmosphere! Not a big fan of their breakfast food but everything else is quite nice.
Loved the caviar pasta, service was really friendly and very cool cutleries.
Unexpectedly good food for a more ulu location
Good brunch, okay desserts. Salad portions are small even for my wife (the one with scallops is at least)
A regular and a favourite
Was fancy a place but ultimately falls short on quality for that price.
Great selection of crowd pleasing foods, plated and served well. Had their set lunch for $12 . Ample serving with mushroom salad appetizer followed by mains. Good job.
The service is quite good, there were times where the staff were helpful and took initiative. However, I find the food a bit pricey - even for cafe standards.

Came back again. The d√©cor has changed drastically and it now looks like a nursery. Very child friendly indeed. Food quality and service still great. Particularly liked the roasted tomato that was thoroughly roasted instead of just charred on top. Meatballs were tasty as well.  Service is attentive and responsive. Once we sat ourselves, a test tube rack with tubes of juice was placed on our table along with breakers of water. Good start. Menu is super cute and nerdy centring around their own version of the periodic table. I had the eggs Florentine. Hollandaise was well made and tasty. I asked for the bacon fried until crispy and it was done to satisfaction. There was a lot of spinach with a (good) surprising hint of garlic. The eggs were slightly more cooked than expected though, but still acceptable. Messy breakfast was quite large and worth it as well. Interesting bacon wrapped pineapple and roasted sweet potato. And they have mustard upon request! They have a unique selection of teas and beers too. Will definitely be back.
Nice ambience. Tasty food at reasonable price (set lunch). Try the chicken main.
Good set lunch. Value for money

Cool presentation. Very laboratory orientated restaurant. Drinks are served in breakers and the tester juices are served in test tubes. Food is in quite large portions. Juices are nice and very tasty. Only problem is that it is not that cheap. Most meals start at around $18 and up
Nice seating place
Nice place

Poor serving sequence. Kids meal, Sparky Dog took so long that the adults food are finished before the kids meal is served. No advance notice/warning given. And they served meals to 2 other tables before our kids meal is served.
tried their pancake.. it was ok... enjoyed their breakfast set better.
Nice selection of juices and cakes. Good place to chill out with friends.
Very original
Nice food. Mostly breakfast and pastas.
Very tasty food
awesome fish and chips! service was really good as well!! will go back next time for desserts hahaha
Good burgers, friendly staff. Will return again
The food is decent (nothing to rave about). The patty on the burger could have been better seasoned. The service was very prompt.
Nice ambience.

Where do I begin...to summarise, probably the best caf√© breakfast we have had in Singapore. We had Eggs Benedict and Messy Breakfast, a capuccino and a mocha. Real bacon, truffle oil scramble eggs, english style sausages, and a yummy salad. The atmosphere is lovely, staff were friendly, food was great, drinks were great, price was reasonable. The small touches from the goldfish biscuits to the test tube juices added to the experience because they had got the basics right. We will definitely come back!
Good offerings of fresh fruit available in a lab environment!
Good cakes!

Interesting presentation of juices - served in test tubes! Seems like the neighborhood flocks here on Sundays so expect noise levels and energy to be high. Overall pricey for the quality and quantity of food you are getting. The dessert was not bad. Breakfast wasn't very memorable.
Hippy place

Nice place for a weekend brunch. They have the usual eggs Benedict or English breakfast with a twist of posh salad. Cakes are also nice. Service gets overwhelmed when quite busy, your order may not get through or food comes late.
Great outdoor seating
Went there on a friday evening . Not so crowded. Very very nice ambience and equally good Service. There was a uniqueness in the way they served water and juices. Definitely will come again...
Interesting juices and good meals, a bit pricey though
AlwaYs lovely.. and friendly

simple tasty food, great service with superb ambience. unlike its name though the food did not have too much of a fruit theme going for it. the lunch dealat $12+ with a main, a salad and  a drink is great value
I know the juice is the star, but the steaks and innis&gunn beer stole the show
Food was actually not bad and as the name suggests, the fruit juices offered by FFL were rather refreshing and crafty, Instagram worthy though. Downside of it is probably the slightly steep price.

Food was not bad, satisfying, portion just nice, but nothing out of this world Theme is real cute, fruit samples were sweet, but the other drinks were so expensive and we didn't know what they were ( what they looked like ) so we didn't dare to buy any Would be nice if the menu had pictures Felt it was mostly the senior lady who was friendly, would love it if the other staff was as friendly or sincere as her Only slightly bad thing was that the red velvet cheesecake wasn't fresh, could tell that it was stored for a little too long as it had a taste to it. Recommended!!! 3.5 rating
Great cafe, good food.
Unique theme.  Great truffle fries and soft shell crab burger.  Tad pricey, but overall satisfying experience

Thank you....wish you further success.

Truffle fries: hard to go wrong with this (: Wings: decent wings but nothing too special Seafood pizza: great for seafood fans! Soft shell chilli crab penne: love how it was served piping hot and managed to stay that way till the last bite thanks to the generous amount of sauce. Would have liked it better if the chilli sauce was spicier Apple barley tea: not sure if I read the drink right but it tasted more like coffee rather than barley. Interesting blend though Service: visited on a quiet weekday night and was nicely taken care of by the staff Ambience: super Instagram friendly cafe. There are wvwn props provided at every table

Quite a cozy place to chill with friends. Good spread of food throughout the day and as the name suggest, they do have fruits platter. All customers are given a test tube of drink and it comes in different juices. They do have beer too! Ask for their promotion as they usually don't indicate it.

A rather interesting place for Sunday Brunch - they're open from 10am and I like that they serve a sampling of their juices in such cute test-tube samplers.   As the name suggests, Fresh Fruits Lab styles its decor and food presentation like a laboratory, and has all things related to science, right down to their gag toys.  Diners are invited to fool around with the toys while waiting for their meal to be served.  Not long to wait though, as FFL's service is both prompt and efficient.  The food is very well done - truffle fries came crisp and fragrant, and our brunch portions were huge.  The Messy Breakfast is utterly delicious - I love the fresh sausages (as opposed to frozen or canned) which are juicy and not overly processed (into a smooth paste) so you can taste and feel the bits of meat.  The winner though, hands down, are the bacon-wrapped pineapple cores, which are heavenly with the smoky salty flavor from the bacon, coupled with the sweet and slightly sour core of the pineapple, made soft by the cooking process.   Just those bacon-pineapple rolls were enough to make me wish I didn't have to share.   *grin*  Parking on a Sunday, at 11am, is pretty easy.  Loads of space on the road that's just in front of the cafe  (Lorong Marzuki), and best of all, since its Sunday, its FREE PARKING!   Popular with couples and families with young kids, and surprisingly, despite all the glass test tubes and beakers of water on the table, there were no "accidents"

Adorable little cafe in the middle of nowhere! They know exactly that you are going to take a billion photos so they have props all over your table to use (stethoscopes, little paper crowns etc.) Free Wifi! (FFL_Guest, PW: freshfruitslab) Complimentary test tube of FRUIT JUICE per person All the drinks are laboratory equipment themed. Your juice comes in flasks, water in beakers.

This place reminds you of your chemistry classes. Everything is in test tube, conical flasks, measuring cups etc. fruit juice in test tube was given complimentary.  Con: parking facilities are limited. They are mostly parallel parking. It is one of those place that you need a car to visit.
Decent food and place. Good service. Coffee was rather disappointing.
Nice environment especially on a cool raining day. Food is not bad and not expensive, just regular cafe pricing. It's a great hang out place during the weekend with family or friends.

The popular salad-fruit cup is really really really sweet.

Good food in very generous portions. Truffle scrambled eggs are excellent - creamy and full of flavor. Juices are a priced a little too high, considering the little that's served. A must-go if you're in the east.

Fairly normal caf√© in Singapore. Can be really packed at random times so be aware. Couldn't tell the difference between the staff, whom look like they've their around home clothes on, and the customers...for some people it is good so enjoy. Finally is the music, they just play Spotify with ads...

Location: little bit harder to get to. Service: Excellent. Love the very casual, familiar, and effortless service. Staff were not rushed, and knew their stuff. It wasn't overly formal, very relaxed atmosphere. I love that they have a copy of the menu on the tables, I really dislike waiting for menus to be brought over, and I love that they serve water and a small portion of juice upfront - very nice touches. Food: Big heart warming plates of comforting breakfast food. Not a huge fan of truffled scrambled eggs, but it was alright. Thankfully they had mustard sauce to go with the otherwise lonely sausages. Rest of it was lovely. The fruits used give a very nice sweet burst of flavor.  Will definitely be back again.
cool concept and complimentary juice shots served in tubes. items are priced reasonably and food are fresh and delicious.
